Rapid Transit - Bomb/Defuse
Made by Foofinoo


On August the 8th, 2016, due to years of neglected maintenance, parts of the Bergmann fresh water tunnel system finally collapsed, in turn causing significant damage and flooding to various subterranean structures.

Due to the blockage of the tunnels, an unusually high amount of pressure was put on the already derelict Two Gorges Dam, and around 20:00 the dam failed catastrophically.

The resulting flood forced the evacuation of Stalburg, and ended up submerging various sites within the river valley including parts of the city itself.

However, these recent events have not stopped local terrorists from trying to take control of Stalburg by pushing the city further into collapse.

Their next stop is the Stenhill metro station...


This map has been in development for the past five months.
Initially started as a fun little "remake" project, it quickly became bigger and bigger over time.

You may have recognized it from the name, this is based on the classic map from Counter-Strike 1.6 made by Cayle George and Jake Anderson, namely DE_RapidTransit.
If you are interested in this remake development and the process of making it, I have been keeping a WIP page right here on GameBanana, so feel free to give it a look for more information.

Just like my last map, CS_Biodome, most of the assets are custom content for a total change of scenery.
This time, they are coming from the amazing game called INFRA by Loiste Interactive.
I've been completely grasped by it, and I thought that it would be cool to make a map with such great assets - even more so a subway map!

Therefore, I have tried to stick as much as possible to the original map layout, while also taking into account the deep and rich lore of INFRA.
I guess it will fly over most people's head, but there are quite some little eater eggs and fun things scattered all over the map...
By the way, a special thanks to Amaruq for allowing me to use his funny Tom's Movies Posters!

I really hope you will enjoy the map as much as I had fun making it!


Foofinoo

This map evolved from one of my older projects. Initially it was a hostage rescue map. But I decided to keep things simpler. Uses assets from BM Source mod and S.T.A.L.K.E.R. (SDK version). The school building itself, materials on buildings, asphalt textures as well as a bunch of original graffiti decals are mine. I used the real world photographs I made of a real school in the city of Donetsk. Skybox and env settings were borrowed from cs_havana. 3D skybox is based on standard HL2 assets, so it does not reflect the real location layout.

This is a beta release, so all comments and suggestions are welcome.

originally I was gonna quit mapping for awhile after releasing viridis. however, that only lasted a couple days lol. not too sure what made me want to make this but nonetheless, here it is.

map is loosely set in "rome". I did look at real pictures and locations when making some of these but they're more or less inspired by them instead of copying. also yes I know the houses kind of look like hotels/motels. don't hate me.

map features 4 stages

stage 1 - poor mans st peters square
stage 2 - road/neighborhood with a roman villa in the center
stage 3 - outside of a pantheon in rome
stage 4 - inside the pantheon. honestly the theme for this stage isn't as unique as the others ones, but it still looks good. I also added a little "visitors" center at the end of it lol. The end of stage 4 is a small little neighborhood with houses as well.
bonus - looks the same as stage 4

Not entirely sure what an optimized run of this could be. Samurai got around 1:20 unoptimized with stages 1-3, so i'm going to assume it'll be around 1:50. bonus is around 15-20 seconds.

lastly, in my opinion, the map looks better when its slightly darker. I would put it around 40-50% brightness

On the outskirts of New York, drug labs have been set up in an effort to make some side cash for Phoenix in the hopes that buying items of mass destruction will be a little easier. A drug bust was set up by the FBI in hopes of apprehending the suspected Phoenix members. Not only did they get proof of Illicit substances but they've kidnapped 2 of the agents for ransom. Needless to say we think they've decided to "turn themselves in".  Counter Terrorists will be sent via helicopter and are tasked with storming the building and bringing the agents across the street where the FBI have an undercover truck prepared to secure them. How the mission turns out is up to you.

Drubust is a short, fast paced Hostage Rescue map and is my first CS map. I have fumbled with Hammer before so needless to say I'm a little impressed with my results. The map is mostly artpassed so unless your looking for issues, you most likely won't find any. I once had planned for T side to have a dig site leading into the subway which is what the subway entrances were for. I canned that because i thought the map didn't need it. I might bring it back in a future version when i decide to work on that.

Needless to say I'm glad i could get 1 less little art piece off of my folder of source crap. Hope you enjoy.

Made in less than 5 days for the LOST HOLES adaptive bots server.

No radar, but it's so small and easy to navigate + it has great call out points.

Both of the spawns are symmetrical and there are 4 distinctive rooms in the side hallways. I have labeled what they are if you don't what to call them. There are also a lot of props that you can destroy! I hope you enjoy my small map!
